sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1992004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: All parts were taken form the iGEM kit
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
introduction Tar chemoreceptor is one of four native chemoreceptors of E.coli, it is mediate chemotaxis response towards aspartate and away from Ni and Co (1). This device allows the expression of a functionally native Tar chemoreceptor.
usage and biology This device constructed from strong promoter (J23100) and RBS (B0034) ensuring high expression of Tar chemoreceptor. High expression of a sole chemoreceptor increase the sensitivity of the bacteria to the substances that interacts with this receptor (מקור). This property makes the system efficient and useful even in low concentrations of desired materials.
expriments and results In order to test the device it was cloned to chemoreceptor free strain (UU1250) and tested for chemotaxis ability using swarming assay. As can be seen in figure 1 the cells expressing the Tar chemoreceptor create a halo indicating a functional chemotaxis result, which compared to the negative and positive controls. The halo can be seen in a matter of hours ensuring that the halo is a result of a chemotaxis response.
Figure 1
Fig1. (a) Tar expression in UU1250 strain, resulting a halo indicating a functional chemotaxis response. (b) Negative control- UU1250 strain w/o the Tar expression plasmid. (c) positive control - ΔZ strain expressing all chemoreceptors.
The part was successfully sequenced (fig2) ensuring the present of the promoter, RBS, Tar receptor and terminator.
Figure 2
Fig 2. (a) Sequencing chromatogram of the K1992004 BioBrick- the RBS is marked. (b) The alignment of the sequencing results in compared to the designed sequence - alignment was done using snapgene software.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tzila Davidov

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K777000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The part was amplified from genomic DNA of E. coli str. K-12 substr. DH10B chromosome (NC_010473.1).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The transmembrane receptor Tar of E. coli mediates chemotaxis towards aspartate.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: One XbaI site was found at position 420. The restriction site was changed from TCTAGt to CCTAGt via QuikChange PCR.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Bianca Genenncher

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg
